{
  "description": "STUDIO-COPILOT-01 (ADR-0060, REV-10) golden corpus for parseAuthoringResult + buildAuthoringPrompt. `accept` entries are valid model outputs that MUST pass schema validation; `reject` entries are malformed/unsafe outputs (wrong shape, empty batch, injection echoes, refusals, pure-markup prompts) that MUST raise StudioValidationError. `output` is the raw model response string. `inject` entries feed buildAuthoringPrompt to assert injection control noise is stripped from the topic and the DATA-framing/topic-fence hardening holds. `outputInject` entries are model outputs carrying an injected XSS/scheme/control/bidi payload smuggled inside otherwise schema-valid question text — the hardened parser MUST neutralise the payload in the surfaced draft (mustNotSurface) while keeping the question usable (expectDrafts), proving no raw model text reaches the client. Expanded for SEC-STUDIO-PROMPT-01 / Pentest #6 AI-safety scope.",
